      "writtenOn": "2016-10-12T20:30:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I notice you did all of your styling on the enter() selector.  This means that if the data updates and say, a task goes from running to done, the style won\u0027t be updated to go from yellow to green (or whatever the colors are)\n\nYou should only apply the fixed styles after the .enter() and then do any dynamic styles on an update selector:\n\nvar data \u003d svg.select(...).data(...);\ndata.enter().append(\"svg...\").attr(\"rx\", \"4\").attr(\"ry\", \"4\") ...\n\n// the un-named, yet super important update selector\ndata.attr(\"width\", function(data) { return data.width; })...",
      "revId": "ff675e00d1e7cf4e23cec1af661fd897f961c2f5",
